Note:
Runa Standard Library: CSV Module

Provides comprehensive CSV file reading and writing, dialect support, streaming, quoting/escaping,
robust error handling, schema validation, and AI/agent-friendly interfaces.

Features:
- Read/write CSV files and streams
- Dialect support (delimiter, quotechar, escapechar, line terminator)
- Streaming and chunked processing
- Quoting, escaping, and edge case handling
- Header and schema validation
- Type conversion and custom parsing
- Error handling and reporting
- AI/agent-friendly interfaces
:End Note

Note: Core Types and Constants
Type CSVDialect is Dictionary with:
    delimiter as String defaults to ","
    quotechar as String defaults to '"'
    escapechar as String defaults to '\\'
    lineterminator as String defaults to "\n"
    doublequote as Boolean defaults to true
    skipinitialspace as Boolean defaults to false
    strict as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CSVReaderOptions is Dictionary with:
    dialect as CSVDialect
    has_header as Boolean defaults to true
    encoding as String defaults to "utf-8"
    chunk_size as Optional[Integer]
    schema as Optional[Dictionary[String, String]]
    ai_mode as Boolean defaults to false

Type CSVWriterOptions is Dictionary with:
    dialect as CSVDialect
    write_header as Boolean defaults to true
    encoding as String defaults to "utf-8"
    ai_mode as Boolean defaults to false

Type CSVRow is Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CSVResult is:
    | CSVSuccess with rows as List[CSVRow]
    | CSVError with message as String and code as String

Note: Core CSV Functions
Process called "read_csv" that takes path as String and options as CSVReaderOptions returns CSVResult:
    Note: Implementation reads CSV file and returns rows
    Return CSVError with message as "Not implemented" and code as "NOT_IMPLEMENTED"

Process called "write_csv" that takes path as String and rows as List[CSVRow] and options as CSVWriterOptions returns Boolean:
    Note: Implementation writes rows to CSV file
    Return false

Process called "parse_csv_string" that takes csv_string as String and options as CSVReaderOptions returns CSVResult:
    Note: Implementation parses CSV string
    Return CSVError with message as "Not implemented" and code as "NOT_IMPLEMENTED"

Process called "generate_csv_string" that takes rows as List[CSVRow] and options as CSVWriterOptions returns String:
    Note: Implementation generates CSV string
    Return ""

Process called "validate_csv_schema" that takes rows as List[CSVRow] and schema as Dictionary[String, String] returns Boolean:
    Note: Implementation validates rows against schema
    Return true

Process called "detect_dialect" that takes sample as String returns CSVDialect:
    Note: Implementation detects CSV dialect from sample
    Return CSVDialect with:
        delimiter as ","
        quotechar as '"'
        escapechar as '\\'
        lineterminator as "\n"
        doublequote as true
        skipinitialspace as false
        strict as false
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "stream_csv" that takes path as String and options as CSVReaderOptions and callback as Process returns None:
    Note: Implementation streams CSV rows and calls callback
    Return None

Process called "create_csv_reader_options" returns CSVReaderOptions:
    Return CSVReaderOptions with:
        dialect as CSVDialect with:
            delimiter as ","
            quotechar as '"'
            escapechar as '\\'
            lineterminator as "\n"
            doublequote as true
            skipinitialspace as false
            strict as false
            metadata as dictionary containing
        has_header as true
        encoding as "utf-8"
        chunk_size as None
        schema as None
        ai_mode as false

Process called "create_csv_writer_options" returns CSVWriterOptions:
    Return CSVWriterOptions with:
        dialect as CSVDialect with:
            delimiter as ","
            quotechar as '"'
            escapechar as '\\'
            lineterminator as "\n"
            doublequote as true
            skipinitialspace as false
            strict as false
            metadata as dictionary containing
        write_header as true
        encoding as "utf-8"
        ai_mode as false

Process called "Some" that takes value as Any returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Implementation depends on core optional types
    Return None

Process called "None" returns Optional[Any]:
    Note: Implementation depends on core optional types
    Return None 